  "ground_truth_procedure": "Respiratory Ventilation, 24-96 Consecutive Hours",
  "guidelines_context": "KDIGO AKI Guidelines 2012 (updated 2024): AKI defined as serum creatinine rise >=0.3 mg/dL within 48h or >=1.5x baseline within 7 days. Indications for renal replacement therapy (RRT): (1) Refractory hyperkalemia K+>6.5 mEq/L or rapidly rising; (2) Metabolic acidosis pH<7.15 refractory to treatment; (3) Volume overload refractory to diuretics causing organ compromise; (4) Uremic encephalopathy, pericarditis, or neuropathy; (5) BUN>100 with uremic symptoms. ATN (acute tubular necrosis) distinguished by urine microscopy showing granular/muddy brown casts, FENa>2%, BUN:Cr ratio <20. Staging: Stage 1 Cr 1.5-1.9x baseline, Stage 2 Cr 2.0-2.9x baseline, Stage 3 Cr >=3x baseline or initiation of RRT. For AKI with tumor lysis syndrome: uric acid, phosphate, potassium elevation are key triggers; rasburicase and RRT indicated when refractory. KDIGO also notes: initiate RRT emergently for life-threatening changes in fluid, electrolyte, and acid-base balance."
